LABEL: obsolete occupation role
definition: A role that has the bearer of a human being and is realized in an occupation process.
term editortrue: Oliver He|Sam Smith|Damion Dooley|John Beverley|Matt Diller

LABEL: obsolete occupation activity
definition: A set of behavioural processes which a person has a disposition to perform repeatedly in pursuit of a social objective.

LABEL: obsolete occupation disposition
definition: A disposition that is held by an occupation holder to perform occupation activity.
term editortrue: Matt Diller|Bill Duncan|Bill Hogan|Oliver He|Sam Smith|John Beverley
